Feature          Test Case         Steps        Expected Results

Feature - Register Account
Test Case - Student enters valid details and submits registration
Steps -
1. Open the system registration page
2. Enter student details
3. Register
Expected Result - account created

Feature - Login
Test Case - Valid Login
Steps - 
1. Enter Student ID
2. Enter Password
3. Click Login
Expected Results - Student enters site

Feature - Book Appointment
Test Case - Student books a clinic appointment successfully
Steps - 
1. Select preferred Doctor
2. Select preferred Date
3. Confirm
Expected Result - account created

Feature - Reschedule Appointment
Test Case - Student reschedules an existing appointment

Steps -

1. Log into the system
2. Open My Appointments
3. Select an existing appointment
4. Choose new available time slot
5. Reschedule

Expected Result - Appointment updated with new time slot

Feature - Cancel Appointment
Test Case - Student cancels an appointment

Steps -

1. Log into the system
2. Open My Appointments
3. Select appointment
4. Click Cancel Appointment

Expected Result - Appointment removed from system

Feature - View Appointment History
Test Case - Student views previous appointments

Steps -

1. Log into the system
2. Navigate to Appointment History
3. View previous appointments

Expected Result - System displays past appointments

Feature - Update Profile
Test Case - Student updates profile information

Steps -

1. Log into the system
2. Open Profile Settings
3. Edit personal information
4. Click Save

Expected Result - Profile updated successfully

Feature - Doctor Login
Test Case - Doctor logs into the system

Steps -

1. Open doctor login page
2. Enter doctor username
3. Enter password
4. Click Login

Expected Result - Doctor dashboard opens successfully

Feature - View Daily Appointments
Test Case - Doctor views list of daily appointments

Steps -

1. Log into doctor dashboard
2. Open Daily Appointments section
3. Select today's date

Expected Result - List of today's appointments displayed

Feature - Add Consultation Notes
Test Case - Doctor adds notes to patient record

Steps -

1. Log into doctor dashboard
2. Select patient appointment
3. Enter consultation notes
4. Click Save

Expected Result - Consultation notes saved successfully

Feature - Admin Login
Test Case - Admin logs into system dashboard

Steps -

1. Open admin login page
2. Enter admin username
3. Enter admin password
4. Click Login

Expected Result - Admin dashboard opens successfully

Feature - Manage Student Accounts
Test Case - Admin adds or edits student accounts

Steps -

1. Log into admin dashboard
2. Navigate to Student Accounts
3. Add or edit student information
4. Click Save

Expected Result - Student account updated successfully

Feature - Generate Appointment Report
Test Case - Admin generates appointment report

Steps -

1. Log into admin dashboard
2. Open Appointment List
3. Click Generate Report

Expected Result - Appointment report generated successfully





